{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2012].
  {panel}

The size of the issue navigator form is getting unwieldy. 

We should reduce the size of the form by moving it into a series of tabs. The initial thoughts for tabs are Project, Constants, Dates, Users and Custom Fields.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
*NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1991].
{panel}
As JIRA Administrator I need the ability to create custom fields for project in pretty much the same way as for issues. This way I will be able to store additional information per project and search for projects and issues based on these additional criteria.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1984].
  {panel}

All current notifications are related to operations on issue.

Some project related events might be interesting to be notified of. The most obvious I see is 'Version Released' but other could be interesting such as version archived, component added, component removed, ...

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1981].
  {panel}

Whilst the addition of new functionality to allow multiple permissions to be added to a group in one transaction is very useful, it would be even better if 1 or more permission can be added to multiple groups in one hit. 

I spotted this when I was trying to add the new permissions of "Schedule Issues" and "Move issues" to existing groups, and at present I have to do each group (of which we have many!) in turn.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1973].
  {panel}


It is possible (in version 2.3x) to filter issues by the issue Reporter, the issue Assignee, and the issue Update date, but not by the issue Updater. 

It would be interesting to have a filter that lets the user see the issues that have been modified by a certain specific user.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1971].
  {panel}

Would like to be able to change a resolution before closing an issue.

e.g. we have a resolution of "Awaiting Validation" and it would be nice, if the validation is successful, to change this to Fixed before we close the issue.

Ideally we would like to be able to add statuses - I will raise this in a separate issue following this one.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1946].
  {panel}

an automated work log feature would be great. If I start work on an issue, I'd click start and JIRA stops recording time for the previos issue (if any) and starts time trackking for the new one. I should be able to add a comment to the first / final / any time record and maybe adjust recorded times (in case I simply forgot to stop recoding before going home!) Since we are still a small team, we do have many interruptions and issue switches during a day.

-- Kai Bounin

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1940].
  {panel}

In the administration part of JIRA it is possible to enable/disable the ability to create unassigned issues. This is now done globally and therefore affects all projects, but it should be possible to do this on a project level.

This could be extended further so it actually resembles the global permissions vs. the project specific permissions, so that every global option also could be decided on a project level (Allow users to vote on issues, Allow users to watch issues, Allow Attachments, Allow unassigned issues, etc).

-- Thomas Watson

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1924].
  {panel}

When performing an upgrade, it would be nice to be able to put Jira into read-only mode.  It takes a long time (10-15m) for the XML import to run now so currently this is downtime for the users because we have to shut down the existing instance.  If we could put the existing instance into read-only mode, then run up the new installation, import the data and then switch, we could have an (almost) completely seamless upgrade.

-- Michael Brown

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1917].
  {panel}

We need to implement concurrency controls for update functions.

-- Edwin
